Although bats carry many characteristics that favor the spread of viruses, the chance of human contact with bats and other wildlife species can be reduced if humans adopt a culture that obliges them to stay away from them.
Continuous monitoring of mammals is essential to better understand the environment of coronaviruses and their natural hosts, which proves useful in preventing animal-to-human transmission and future outbreaks.
