Chinese New Year celebrations (January 25) were cancelled in several places.
Authorities also announced the construction of a temporary hospital, Huoshinshan Hospital, which was completed within 10 days.
Another hospital was then built, Lishenshan Hospital, to deal with the additional patients.
In addition to the newly established hospitals, China has also converted 14 other facilities in Wuhan, such as convention centers and stadiums, into temporary hospitals. On 26 January, the government took other measures to contain the COVID-19 outbreak, including introducing health announcements for travelers and extending the Spring Festival holiday.
Universities and schools were also closed across the country.
The Hong Kong and Macao regions have taken several measures, particularly with regard to schools and universities.
Teleworking measures have been taken in several Chinese regions.
