Of the 35 patients in Shenzhen, the test results were negative on an average of 4 days, while the duration of the illness was 11 days in 45 patients who did not receive it.
In a study in Wuhan of 240 patients with pneumonia, half were given faviperavir and the other half received omiphenovir.
The Italian Medicines Agency has warned people that existing evidence supporting the drug is incomplete and preliminary.
